      • getGraphWithBeeLine

        public Map<Node,​Map<Node,​Double>> getGraphWithBeeLine()
        Builds the following Graph A-B-C . | | D-E-F . | | G-H-I

        Weights: . A B C D E F G H I A 0 1 B 1 1 5 C 1 1 D 5 E 5 5 1 5 F 1 1 1 G 1 H 5 1 1 I 1 1

        Start A End G Expected Path {A,B,E,H,G} (best with bee line) Expected Path 2 {A,B,C,F,I,H,G} (best with shortest path) uses estimate with bee line instead of shortest path

        Returns:
        graph that uses bee line for path finding

      • getGraphWithTwoEqualPaths

        public Map<Node,​Map<Node,​Double>> getGraphWithTwoEqualPaths()

        A | \ B C | / D

        Start A End D Shortest Path {A,B,D}, {A,C,D}

        Returns:
        graph with two equally good paths
